(70, 34, 'Content', '\r\n                   <p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"margin-top: 0px\">My name is Baba Solomon. I was born in 1973 in Antsirabe, \r\n                         the city of pousse-pousse and thermal sources.  I am member of the Merina tribe from \r\n                         the high plateaux of Madagascar. I studied economics and tourism from 1995 until 1999.\r\n                         My favorite sports are swimming, cycling, martial arts and hiking. Since 2002 I am working \r\n                         as a driver guide and car rental.</p>\r\n                  <p class=\"text-justify\">I decided to start my own tour company which is based in Antsirabe by the licence <span style=\"color: #5bc6fe\">N°027-13/MINTOUR/SG/DGDT/DAIT/SAT</span>. \r\n                    I travelled with tourists from several countries like the Netherlands, Germany, Italy,\r\n                         Japan, Spain, and the USA. Beyond Malagasy, I speak English, Spanish and French. \r\n                         When the toutrist season is finished I work for a project to help the children in \r\n                         the country side. I hope see you soon in Madagascar.</p>\r\n                    \r\n                <h4 class=\"title-4\">Colleague</h4>\r\n                <p class=\"fontRegular\">\r\n                  We are all Malagasy, the drivers and guides as well as the manager who have their \r\n                         own experience, which means that it is a Madagascar local company.                </p>', 'html', 'en', 2, 1, '2025-12-01 04:37:01', '2025-12-01 04:37:01'),
(71, 34, 'Content spanish', '\r\n                   <p class=\"text-justify\" style=\"margin-top: 0px\">Me llamo Baba Solomon. Nací en 1973 en Antsirabe, \r\n                         la ciudad del pousse-pousse y las fuentes termales.  Pertenezco a la tribu merina de \r\n                         de las altas mesetas de Madagascar. Estudié economía y turismo de 1995 a 1999.\r\n                         Mis deportes favoritos son la natación, el ciclismo, las artes marciales y el senderismo. Desde 2002 trabajo \r\n                         como conductor guía y alquiler de coches.</p>\r\n                  <p class=\"text-justify\">Decidí crear mi propia empresa de turismo, con sede en Antsirabe, junto a la licencia <span style=\"color: #5bc6fe\">N°027-13/MINTOUR/SG/DGDT/DAIT/SAT</span>. \r\n                    Viajé con turistas de varios países como los Países Bajos, Alemania, Italia,\r\n                         Japón, España y Estados Unidos. Además de malgache, hablo inglés, español y francés. \r\n                         Cuando termina la temporada turística, trabajo en un proyecto para ayudar a los niños del campo. \r\n                         en el campo. Espero verte pronto en Madagascar.</p>\r\n                    \r\n                <h4 class=\"title-4\">Colega</h4>\r\n                <p class=\"fontRegular\">\r\n                  Todos somos malgaches, tanto los conductores y guías como el gerente, que tienen su propia experiencia, lo que significa que es una empresa local de Madagascar. \r\n                         propia experiencia, lo que significa que es una empresa local de Madagascar.                </p>', 'html', 'es', 3, 1, '2025-12-01 04:40:30', '2025-12-01 04:40:30'),
(72, 34, 'Content 2', '<p>Below you find (in alphabetical order) information to help you to prepare your holiday.\r\n                         For more information you can always contact us.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">ATM</h4>\r\n      <p>There are ATMs in all major cities. Getting money from an ATM is only \r\n                         possible with a credit card. A Visa card is most convenient.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Currency</h4>\r\n      <iframe loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://usd.currencyrate.today/mga\" name=\"guestbook\" scrolling=\"no\" width=\"100%\" height=\"750\" frameborder=\"no\"></iframe>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Electricity</h4>\r\n      <p>220 volts, keep in mind that the stream can sometimes fail.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Health</h4>\r\n      <p class=\"fontRegular\">Depending on the country of origin a vaccination against cholera (or just a stamp) is required. \r\n                         For further information on vaccinations and malaria prevention we refer you to a relevant service \r\n                         in your country. We recommend you not to drink tap water, bottled mineral water is widely available.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Internet</h4>\r\n      <p class=\"fontRegular\">There are cyber cafes in the major cities. Some hotels offer internet \r\n                         facilities as well. Generally the internet in cyber cafes is cheap, the \r\n                         speed of the connection varies.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Passport</h4>\r\n      <p class=\"fontRegular\">You must be in possession of a passport which is valid for at least 6 months upon departure from Madagascar.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Phone</h4>\r\n      <p class=\"fontRegular\">You can get a very cheap SIM card in Madagascar. Probably its a lot  cheaper to use this \r\n                         instead calling with you own SIM card. There are several providers, including Orange, Telma and Airtel.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Photography and filming</h4>\r\n      <p class=\"fontRegular\">Because of the varied landscape and lots of animals you probably make \r\n                         many pictures in Madagascar. Also in the cities and on the way there are\r\n                         many moments you want to capture. We advise you to ask permission when \r\n                         you want to photograph of film the local people. Sometimes the people \r\n                         ask you to send them the pictures. It would be very appreciated when you do this.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Restaurants</h4>\r\n      <p class=\"fontRegular\">Restaurant come in all varieties. Besides traditional Malagasy \r\n                         restaurants there are for instance Italian, Chinese and Indian  restaurants.<br>\r\n                         For breakfast you pay about 5 euro, for lunch and diner about 10 euro. \r\n                         But for a lot less you can have good food as well.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Safety</h4>\r\n      <p class=\"fontRegular\">In general, the Malagasy are honest people, but there are always people \r\n                         with bad intentions. The major cities in Madagascar are not less safe \r\n                         than a large western city. Of course you can be robbed like that could \r\n                         happen anywhere, but with a little common sense you can greatly reduce \r\n                         the chance of this. Don’t wear expensive or flashy jewelry and wear a \r\n                         moneybelt under your clothes. In Antananarivo we advice you to take a \r\n                         taxi in the evening. Make a copy or scan of your important documents, \r\n                         this way it’s easier to replace them after loss or theft.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Visa</h4>\r\n      <p>A visa up to 1 month you can get (at the moment for free) at arrival at \r\n                         the airport. A visa up to 3 month is also available at the airport, but not for free.</p>\r\n      <p class=\"fontRegular\"></p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0\">What should not be missing in your luggage</h4>\r\n      <p style=\"text-align: justify;\" class=\"fontRegular\">Keep in mind when you pack your clothes temperatures may be very different.<br>\r\n                         Even in places where it\'s warm during the day, the evenings can be cool.<br>\r\n                         Furthermore are recommended:<br>walking shoes,<br>sandals/flipflops,\r\n                         <br> thin rain jacket/poncho,<br>sun hat/cap,</p>', 'html', 'en', 3, 1, '2025-12-01 09:29:22', '2025-12-01 09:29:22'),
(73, 34, 'Content 2 Spanish', ' <p>A continuación encontrará (por orden alfabético) información que le ayudará a preparar sus vacaciones.\r\n                         Para más información, siempre puede ponerse en contacto con nosotros.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">ATM</h4>\r\n      <p>Hay cajeros automáticos en las principales ciudades. Sólo se puede sacar dinero de un cajero \r\n                         es posible con una tarjeta de crédito. La tarjeta Visa es la más conveniente.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Moneda</h4>\r\n      <iframe loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://usd.currencyrate.today/mga\" name=\"guestbook\" scrolling=\"no\" width=\"100%\" height=\"750\" frameborder=\"no\"></iframe>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Electricidad</h4>\r\n      <p>220 voltios, tenga en cuenta que la corriente a veces puede fallar.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Salud</h4>\r\n      <p class=\"fontRegular\">Dependiendo del país de origen, se exige una vacuna contra el cólera (o simplemente un sello). \r\n                         Para más información sobre vacunas y prevención de la malaria, le remitimos a un servicio pertinente \r\n                         de su país. Le recomendamos que no beba agua del grifo; el agua mineral embotellada está ampliamente disponible.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Internet</h4>\r\n      <p class=\"fontRegular\">Hay cibercafés en las principales ciudades. Algunos hoteles también \r\n                         Internet. Por lo general, Internet en los cibercafés es barato. \r\n                         velocidad de la conexión varía.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Pasaporte</h4>\r\n      <p class=\"fontRegular\">Debe estar en posesión de un pasaporte con una validez mínima de 6 meses a la salida de Madagascar.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Teléfono</h4>\r\n      <p class=\"fontRegular\">En Madagascar se puede conseguir una tarjeta SIM muy barata. Probablemente sea mucho más barato \r\n                         en lugar de llamar con tu propia tarjeta SIM. Hay varios proveedores, como Orange, Telma y Airtel.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Fotografía y filmación</h4>\r\n      <p class=\"fontRegular\">Debido a la variedad del paisaje y a la gran cantidad de animales, es probable que haga \r\n                         muchas fotos en Madagascar. También en las ciudades y en el camino hay\r\n                         muchos momentos que querrás capturar. Le aconsejamos que pida permiso \r\n                         cuando quiera fotografiar o filmar a la población local. A veces la gente \r\n                         a veces te piden que les envíes las fotos. Le agradeceremos mucho que lo haga.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Restaurantes</h4>\r\n      <p class=\"fontRegular\">Restaurant come in all varieties. Besides traditional Malagasy \r\n                         restaurants there are for instance Italian, Chinese and Indian restaurants.<br>\r\n                         For breakfast you pay about 5 euro, for lunch and diner about 10 euro. \r\n                         But for a lot less you can have good food as well.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Seguridad</h4>\r\n      <p class=\"fontRegular\">En general, los malgaches son gente honrada, pero siempre hay gente \r\n                         con malas intenciones. Las grandes ciudades de Madagascar no son menos seguras \r\n                         que una gran ciudad occidental. Por supuesto, pueden robarle como en cualquier sitio. \r\n                         ocurrir en cualquier sitio, pero con un poco de sentido común puedes reducir mucho \r\n                         las posibilidades de que esto ocurra. No lleve joyas caras o llamativas y lleve un \r\n                         cinturón para el dinero bajo la ropa. En Antananarivo te aconsejamos que cojas un \r\n                         taxi por la noche. Haz una copia o escanea tus documentos importantes, \r\n                         así será más fácil reponerlos en caso de pérdida o robo.</p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\">Visa</h4>\r\n      <p>Un visado de hasta 1 mes lo puede obtener (de momento gratis) a su llegada al \r\n                         en el aeropuerto. Un visado de hasta 3 meses también está disponible en el aeropuerto, pero no es gratuito.</p>\r\n      <p class=\"fontRegular\"></p>\r\n      <h4 class=\"fontMedium\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0\">Lo que no debe faltar en su equipaje</h4>\r\n      <p style=\"text-align: justify;\" class=\"fontRegular\">Ten en cuenta que cuando empaques tu ropa, las temperaturas pueden ser muy diferentes.<br>\r\n                         Incluso en lugares donde hace calor durante el día, las noches pueden ser frescas.<br>\r\n                         Además se recomienda:<br>zapatos para caminar,<br>sandalias/chanclas,\r\n                         <br> chubasquero/poncho fino,<br>sombrero/gorra para el sol,</p>', 'html', 'es', 4, 1, '2025-12-01 09:30:46', '2025-12-01 09:30:46'),
(74, 35, 'Content', '<h1 class=\"font-inter-bold\">Madagascar Trip Policies and Sales Conditions</h1>\r\n<h2 class=\"sr-only\">Madagascar Trip Policies: Essential Information for Travelers</h2>\r\n        <p class=\"font-inter-regular\"></p><h4 class=\"fontMedium text-success mt-4\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-top: 1.5rem !important;\">Registration and reservation</h4><p class=\"text-justify fontRegular\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 28px;\">Registration or reservation for a circuit organized by Madagascar Green Tours can be done with our customer advisers at our agency in Antsirabe, or by e-mail at info@madagascar-green-tours.com When booking, specific information about the customer (first and last names, dates of birth, flight details, etc.) is required.</p><h4 class=\"fontMedium text-success\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px;\">Price</h4><p class=\"text-justify fontRegular mb-3\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; line-height: 28px; margin-bottom: 1rem !important;\">All tours sold by Madagascar Green Tours are priced in Euros or Dollars per person and cover the current year. The prices of the circuits offered by Madagascar Green Tours include only the services indicated in each offer. The descriptive sheets of Madagascar Green Tours trips and stays mention what is included in the price and what is not.<br>We may find ourselves obliged to modify our prices and our programs to take into account:</p><ul class=\"fontRegular\" style=\"margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none;\"><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none;\">- variations in the cost of transport, linked in particular to the cost of fuel.</li><li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none;\">- changes in fees and taxes relating to the services provided, such as taxes</li></ul